{{Nihongo|'''''Kin Kyori Renai'''''|近キョリ恋愛|Kin Kyori Ren'ai}} is a Japanese [[comedy]] [[romance manga|romance]] ''[[shōjo manga|shōjo]]'' [[manga]] series written and illustrated by Rin Mikimoto.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.manga-news.com/index.php/serie-vo/Kinkyori-Renai-vo|title= Kinkyori Renai vo|accessdate= December 23, 2014|work= manga-news.com|language= French}}</ref>It was adapted into a [[Japanese television drama]] that aired on [[Nippon Television]] from July 19 to October 11, 2014<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.allcinema.net/prog/show_c.php?num_c=349427|title= 近キョリ恋愛　～Season Zero～(2014)|accessdate= December 23, 2014|work= allcinema.net|publisher= Stingray|language= Japanese}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.tvdrama-db.com/drama_info/p/id-56839|title= 近キョリ恋愛～Season Zero～|accessdate= December 23, 2014|work= www.tvdrama-db.com|language= Japanese}}</ref> and into a [[live action]] film that was released on October 11, 2014 in Japan.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2014-04-22/rin-mikimoto-kin-kyori-renai-shojo-manga-gets-live-action-film|title= Rin Mikimoto's Kin Kyori Renai Shōjo Manga Gets Live Action Film|date= 2014-04-22|accessdate= 2014-04-25|work= [[Anime News Network]]}}</ref>

==Characters==
* Haruka Sakurai ([[Tomohisa Yamashita]])
* Yuni Kururugi ([[Nana Komatsu (actress)|Nana Komatsu]])
* Ikuhaba ([[Nozomu Kotaki]])
* Kikuko Nanami ([[Mizuki Yamamoto]])
* Mirei Takizawa ([[Asami Mizukawa]])
* Akachi ([[Hirofumi Arai]])

==Film adaptation==
{{main|Close Range Love (film)}}
A film adaptation was released in 2014. The film has been [[List of 2014 box office number-one films in Japan|number one at the Japanese box office]] for two weeks and has grossed [[Japanese yen|¥]]475 million.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.filmbiz.asia/news/close-range-love-pulls-ahead-in-japan|title= Close Range Love pulls ahead in Japan|author= Kevin Ma|date= October 22, 2014|accessdate= October 23, 2014|work= [[Film Business Asia]]}}</ref>

